Method Detail

onParams

public static <T extends Annotation> List<Map.Entry<T,Object>> onParams(Class<T> type,
                                                                        InvocationContext context)

Finds all parameters on the request definition which are annotated with the given type and returns the annotation instance together with the runtime argument.

Parameters:
type - the Class of the annotation to look for on the request parameters

context - the InvocationContext containing the request definition to extract the metadata from

Returns:
an unmodifiable List of Map.Entry instances with the annotation as the and the runtime argument as the value; note that the implementation of Map.Entry#setValue(Object) throws an UnsupportedOperationException

Since:
1.3.0

findMethod

public static Request.RequestMethod findMethod(Method definition)

Takes the Method definition of a request and discovers the Request.RequestMethod which has been specified using annotated metadata.

Parameters:
definition - the Method definition for the request whose HTTP method is to be discovered

Returns:
the Request.RequestMethod for the given request definition; else null if no Request.RequestMethod metadata can be found

Since:
1.3.0

public static String findPath(Method definition)

Takes the Method definition of a request and discovers the sub-path (if any) which is specified using annotated metadata.

Parameters:
definition - the Method definition for the request whose sub-path is to be discovered

Returns:
the sub-path for the given request definition; else an empty String
